cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.CYBER, cs.RO, cs.HC

Reasoning: 
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on agent-based modeling and simulation of connected and automated vehicles in a multi-agent system.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of a distributed consensus-based protocol for cooperative on-ramp merging, which involves control of the CAVs.
- cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) is a possible category as the paper mentions the use of vehicle-to-everything (V2X) communications, which can involve cybersecurity and privacy concerns.
- cs.RO (Robotics) is a possible category as the paper deals with autonomous vehicles and their interactions with each other and the environment.
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a possible category as the paper compares the results of the proposed protocol with a human-in-the-loop simulation, which involves human-computer interaction.
